description:
&lt;p&gt;This role provides an opportunity to support East Cheshire NHS Trusts community teams in provide harm free, high quality care to their patients,.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will act as a lead champion / coordinator for Falls Prevention across the community services, providing specialist support to the community teams to manage and co-ordinate early intervention/ prevention support for people who are at high risk of falling or those who are repeat fallers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is key to supporting the teams continued professional development assisting them to manage falls effectively within the local population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It requires a focused individual, passionate about falls prevention and management to be able to motivate others to implement change and service developments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The trusts community teams work closely with primary care networks and form part to the care community integrated teams, where this role would sit, providing an opportunity to work closely with key stakeholders across the patient pathway to influence the provision of high quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be an expectation for the individual to work across the five care communities within East Cheshire - which consist of Macclesfield, Knutsford, Congleton &amp; Holmes Chapel, CHAW (Chelford, Handforth, Alderley &amp; Wilmslow) and BDP (Bollington, Disley &amp; Poynton)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will link closely with the acute Falls coordinator role within the trust to further strength patient pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is Fixed Term for 18 months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours per week: 18.75&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 6th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced with Barred list Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Careers website with lots of information on how to join our team and Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Laura Plant Job title Head of Allied Health Professionals Email address laura.plant1@nhs.netTelephone number 01625 663442&lt;/p&gt;
